{# Per-recipient subpoena target document. v0.28.0.

   Renders one subpoena for a specific recipient (CEX, ISP, KYC
   provider, dApp, law enforcement). Body sections mirror the
   freeze_request structure so the legal-review pattern operators
   already know maps 1:1.

   Inputs (via Jinja context):
     * target: a SUBPOENA_TARGETS list element (dict)
     * case_id, brief_id, victim, investigator
     * generated_at (ISO timestamp string)
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Subpoena Target — {{ target.recipient_name }} — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 8.5in; margin: 0.5in auto; padding: 0 0.5in; color: #1f2937; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; }
    h1 { font-size: 18pt; margin-bottom: 0.25em; color: #111827; border-bottom: 2px solid #1f2937; padding-bottom: 0.25em; }
    h2 { font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 1.5em; color: #1f2937; }
    h3 { font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 1em; color: #374151; }
    table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 0.5em 0; font-size: 10pt; }
    th, td { border: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding: 0.4em 0.6em; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
    th { background: #f3f4f6; font-weight: 600; }
    .mono { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 9pt; word-break: break-all; }
    .amount { text-align: right; }
    .pill { display: inline-block; padding: 0.15em 0.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; font-size: 9pt; font-weight: 600; }
    .pill-high { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
    .pill-medium { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }
    .pill-low { background: #f3f4f6; color: #374151; }
    .summary-box { background: #f9fafb; border-left: 4px solid #1f2937; padding: 0.75em 1em; margin: 1em 0; }
    .meta-row { display: flex; gap: 1em; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 0.5em 0; font-size: 10pt; color: #4b5563; }
    .meta-row strong { color: #1f2937; }
    ul { padding-left: 1.5em; }
    li { margin: 0.25em 0; }
    footer { margin-top: 3em; border-top: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding-top: 1em; font-size: 9pt; color: #6b7280; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Subpoena Target — {{ target.recipient_name }}</h1>

{# v0.32.1 (JACOB_FREEZE_LETTER_AUDIT CRIT-ST-1): explicit
   AUSA-signature-required gate at the top of the document. Pre-v0.32.1
   the footer only said "operator-prepared evidence intended for
   judicial / law-enforcement review. Not a public artifact." — that is
   NOT a clear enough gate. A subpoena_target file rendered to PDF and
   accidentally forwarded to a CEX compliance team by a non-lawyer
   operator would be a malpractice-adjacent event. The banner mirrors
   the "DRAFT — For AUSA Review & Issuance Only" treatment on
   subpoena_request.html.j2 (the grand-jury draft template). #}
<div style="margin:0.5em 0 1em 0; padding:0.75em 1em; background:#fee2e2; border:2px solid #991b1b; color:#991b1b; font-weight:700;">
  DRAFT — DO NOT SERVE WITHOUT AUSA SIGNATURE.
  This is an investigator-prepared evidence brief intended to assist an
  Assistant United States Attorney's drafting of a grand-jury subpoena
  duces tecum (or equivalent legal process). Recupero has no subpoena
  authority. This document must NOT be transmitted to the recipient
  until issued on government letterhead and signed by the assigned AUSA
  or other competent issuing authority. Unauthorized transmission may
  constitute unauthorized practice of law.
</div>

<div class="meta-row">
  <span><strong>Case:</strong> {{ case_id }}</span>
  <span><strong>Target ID:</strong> {{ target.target_id }}</span>
  <span><strong>Priority:</strong>
    <span class="pill pill-{{ target.priority|default('medium') }}">{{ target.priority|default('medium')|upper }}</span>
  </span>
  <span><strong>Generated:</strong> {{ generated_at }}</span>
</div>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p>
  This document is a structured record-request brief for
  <strong>{{ target.recipient_name }}</strong>{% if target.recipient_jurisdiction %} ({{ target.recipient_jurisdiction }}){% endif %}.
  In connection with case <code>{{ case_id }}</code>{% if victim and victim.name %} (victim: {{ victim.name }}){% endif %},
  Recupero has identified
  {% if target.linked_addresses|length == 1 %}
    one on-chain address
  {% else %}
    {{ target.linked_addresses|length }} on-chain addresses
  {% endif %}
  that {% if target.evidentiary_basis == 'off_ramp_deposit' %}received perpetrator-controlled funds via {{ target.recipient_name }}'s exchange infrastructure{% elif target.evidentiary_basis == 'non_freezable_seizure_target' %}holds perpetrator-controlled value at non-freezable (permissionless / wrapper) assets{% else %}{{ target.evidentiary_basis|default('') }}{% endif %}.
  The records requested below are intended to surface the
  perpetrator's identity and enable subsequent
  {% if target.recipient_type == 'cex' %}criminal-process referral and seizure{% elif target.recipient_type == 'law_enforcement' %}seizure / arrest{% else %}investigative pivots{% endif %}.
  The expected response window is
  <strong>{{ target.estimated_response_window_days|default(30) }} days</strong>.
</p>

<h2>2. Factual Basis</h2>
<p>
  The on-chain trace anchored at <code>{{ case_id }}</code> identifies the following address(es)
  under {{ target.recipient_name }}'s control:
</p>
{# v0.32.1 (JACOB_FREEZE_LETTER_AUDIT HIGH-ST-2): per-address
   evidence now includes tx_hashes (and observed_at windows + transfer
   count) when the upstream `extract_subpoena_targets` carried them.
   Without transaction-level evidence the CEX compliance team has
   nothing to grep against in their internal records — the subpoena
   gets rejected on review. Chain column kept prominent so a
   multi-chain consolidated subpoena renders the chain for every row,
   not just the case's primary chain. #}
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="width:22em;">Address</th>
      <th style="width:8em;">Chain</th>
      <th>Role</th>
      <th class="amount">Amount (USD) &amp; Transaction Evidence</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for la in target.linked_addresses %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ la.address }}</td>
      <td>{{ la.chain or '—' }}</td>
      <td>{{ la.role }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">
        {% if la.evidence and la.evidence|length > 0 %}
          {% for ev in la.evidence %}
            {% if ev.amount_usd %}${{ '{:,.2f}'.format(ev.amount_usd|float) }}{% endif %}
            {% if ev.transfer_count %}<br><span style="font-size:8pt; color:#4b5563;">across {{ ev.transfer_count }} on-chain transfer{{ "s" if ev.transfer_count != 1 else "" }}</span>{% endif %}
            {% if ev.first_observed_at or ev.last_observed_at %}<br><span style="font-size:8pt; color:#4b5563;">observed: {{ ev.first_observed_at or '?' }} — {{ ev.last_observed_at or '?' }}</span>{% endif %}
            {% if ev.tx_hashes and ev.tx_hashes|length > 0 %}
              <br><span style="font-size:8pt;">Tx hashes:<br>
              {% for h in ev.tx_hashes %}
                <code style="font-size:7pt; word-break: break-all;">{{ h }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}<br>{% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
              </span>
            {% endif %}
            {% if not loop.last %}<br>{% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>
  Each address was identified via on-chain trace from the victim's
  seed address, with provenance recorded in the case's
  <code>case.json</code> and <code>freeze_brief.json</code> sibling
  artifacts. Block-by-block trace evidence is available on request.
</p>

<h2>3. Records Requested</h2>
<p>
  The following records are requested for each address listed in
  section 2:
</p>
<ul>
{% for r in target.expected_records %}
  <li>{{ r }}</li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>4. Legal Authority</h2>
{# v0.32.1 (JACOB_FREEZE_LETTER_AUDIT HIGH-ST-1): correct the
   grand-jury subpoena cite from 18 U.S.C. § 3486 to Federal Rule of
   Criminal Procedure 17(c). Engineering judgment per audit:

   18 U.S.C. § 3486 is the *administrative subpoena* authority for
   specified federal investigations (healthcare fraud, child
   exploitation, controlled substances, terrorism, certain federal
   crimes against the US — 18 U.S.C. § 3486(a)(1)(A)(i)-(iv)). It
   is NOT the general grand-jury subpoena authority. A grand-jury
   subpoena issued under § 3486 for, say, a wire-fraud (18 U.S.C.
   § 1343) predicate would be invalid.

   Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 17(c) is the correct authority
   for a grand-jury subpoena duces tecum directed to a third-party
   record custodian (e.g., a CEX, KYC provider, ISP). That is the
   same authority cited by the parallel `subpoena_request.html.j2`
   template (line 42-43) — the two templates now match.

   Administrative-subpoena and seizure-order branches retained for
   the rare in-scope predicates (HCF, etc.) so the operator can
   override `target.instrument` to `'administrative_subpoena'` and
   the right cite renders. #}
<p>
  <strong>Instrument:</strong>
  {% if target.instrument == 'grand_jury_subpoena' %}Grand jury subpoena <em>duces tecum</em>, pursuant to <strong>Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 17(c)</strong>, to be issued by the assigned Assistant United States Attorney upon impanelment of (or in connection with) a federal grand jury in the judicial district of appropriate venue{% elif target.instrument == 'administrative_subpoena' %}Administrative subpoena pursuant to <strong>18 U.S.C. § 3486</strong> (available only for the federal investigations enumerated in § 3486(a)(1)(A) — healthcare fraud, federal child-exploitation offenses, controlled-substance investigations under 21 U.S.C. § 876, and certain crimes against the United States; verify the predicate falls within § 3486 before relying on this instrument){% elif target.instrument == '2703_d_order' %}Court order pursuant to <strong>18 U.S.C. § 2703(d)</strong> (Stored Communications Act, for non-content records held by an electronic communication service / remote computing service){% elif target.instrument == 'seizure_order' %}Seizure order (post-identification — coordinated with prosecuting agency under 18 U.S.C. § 981 / § 982 civil or criminal forfeiture authority as applicable){% elif target.instrument == 'preservation_letter' %}Preservation request pursuant to <strong>18 U.S.C. § 2703(f)</strong> (90-day records-preservation; preliminary to a § 2703(d) order or Rule 17(c) subpoena){% else %}{{ target.instrument or '(operator to specify the issuing instrument and applicable statutory authority)' }}{% endif %}.
</p>
<p class="small" style="color:#4b5563;">
  <strong>Note on statutory authority.</strong> The cite above is the
  default for the selected <code>instrument</code>; the AUSA or
  competent issuing authority retains final authority over the cite
  used on the issued process. Recupero recommends the AUSA verify the
  cite matches the predicate offense — in particular, 18 U.S.C. § 3486
  is NOT the general grand-jury authority and applies only to the
  enumerated federal investigations in § 3486(a)(1)(A). For
  wire-fraud / money-laundering / general federal predicates, Federal
  Rule of Criminal Procedure 17(c) is the correct grand-jury
  authority.
</p>
<p>
  Delivery: this document is for in-person service or e-mail forwarding
  to the recipient's compliance team{% if target.recipient_compliance_email %}
  at <code>{{ target.recipient_compliance_email }}</code>{% endif %} —
  <strong>only after the AUSA has signed and issued formal process
  on government letterhead</strong>.
  Chain-of-custody verification: every linked address in section 2 is
  verifiable on-chain at the recipient's preferred block explorer.
</p>

<h2>5. Follow-up Pivots</h2>
<p>
  Anticipated follow-up actions based on the records this subpoena
  produces:
</p>
{% if target.follow_up_pivots %}
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>If records show...</th>
      <th>Next target type</th>
      <th>Note</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for pivot in target.follow_up_pivots %}
    <tr>
      <td><code>{{ pivot.if_records_show }}</code></td>
      <td>{{ pivot.next_target_type }}</td>
      <td>{{ pivot.notes or '' }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p><em>No follow-up pivots documented for this target.</em></p>
{% endif %}

<h2>6. Investigator Certification</h2>
<p>
  This document was prepared by Recupero on behalf of
  {% if victim and victim.name %}victim <strong>{{ victim.name }}</strong>{% else %}the case-of-record victim{% endif %}
  in coordination with
  {% if investigator and investigator.name %}<strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong>{% if investigator.organization %} ({{ investigator.organization }}){% endif %}{% else %}the assigned investigator{% endif %}.
  All addresses listed are derived from on-chain BFS trace data
  with full transaction-level evidence retained for forensic
  cross-reference.
</p>
{# v0.32.1 (JACOB_FREEZE_LETTER_AUDIT MED-ST-1): explicit
   no-subpoena-authority disclaimer. Mirrors the language in the
   parallel `subpoena_request.html.j2` template (line 44-46). Without
   this, a reader may infer Recupero has subpoena authority based on
   the document's tone. The investigator's role is to surface
   evidentiary basis — the AUSA's role is to issue the legal
   process. #}
<p style="margin-top:0.75em;">
  <strong>Recupero's role.</strong> Recupero is a private investigation
  service. Recupero has no subpoena authority and does not represent
  itself as having the authority to compel records production from any
  party. This document is provided to assist the assigned AUSA's
  drafting of formal process; the AUSA must issue the final subpoena
  on government letterhead before the records demand is enforceable
  against {{ target.recipient_name }}.
</p>
{% if investigator and investigator.email %}
<p>
  <strong>Investigator contact:</strong>
  <code>{{ investigator.email }}</code>
</p>
{% endif %}

{% if target.depends_on %}
<div class="summary-box">
  <strong>Dependency note.</strong> This subpoena is downstream of
  {{ target.depends_on|length }} prior target(s):
  {% for d in target.depends_on %}<code>{{ d }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}.
  Deliver this only after the dependent records have been received
  and reviewed for the records-show conditions in section 5.
</div>
{% endif %}

<footer>
  Generated by Recupero · Case <code>{{ case_id }}</code> · Target
  <code>{{ target.target_id }}</code> · {{ generated_at }}.
  This document is operator-prepared evidence intended for
  judicial / law-enforcement review. Not a public artifact.
  <br/><br/>
  <strong>DRAFT — DO NOT SERVE WITHOUT AUSA SIGNATURE.</strong>
  Recupero has no subpoena authority. This document is investigator-
  prepared evidence to assist the assigned AUSA's drafting; it must
  not be transmitted to {{ target.recipient_name }} until formal
  process has been issued on government letterhead.
</footer>

</body>
</html>
